<div style="margin: 30px 0; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #5a4e3a; padding: 10px; background: #15120c; box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px #000;">[[File:OnceWasNowIsHouse2.jpg|center|600x600px|A faded yellow house on wooden stilts, surrounded by an endless field of red poppies under a featureless bright sky.]]<div style="color: #9a8a70; font-size: 0.9em; margin-top: 8px;">The house as it first appears.</div></div>

== <span style="border-left: 6px solid #7a6040; padding-left: 15px; color: #d4c4ac; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: 2px;">Description</span> ==
'''Once Was, Now Is''' manifests as a small yellow house elevated on stilts, situated in the centre of an infinitely stretching field littered with blood-red poppies. Despite the absence of a sun, the environment is uniformly illuminated with daylight. A singular cumulus cloud hangs in the sky, but does not move at all.<div style="margin: 30px 0; text-align: center; font-style: italic; color: #bcac94; font-size: 1.6em; text-shadow: 0 2px 4px #000; letter-spacing: 2px;">
<span style="border-top: 1px solid #5a4a36; border-bottom: 1px solid #5a4a36; padding: 10px 30px;">“Once Was Lost, Now Is Found.”</span>
</div>If wanderers choose not to enter the house within 99 '''minutes''' of arriving, the level undergoes a drastic shift. We refer to this state as '''“Once Was Lost, Now Is Found.”''' Entities will begin to appear in their peripheral vision as blurred, muted silhouettes. They perfectly mimic the posture, height, and gait of a loved one, a childhood friend, or a deceased relative. They never speak, but their presence radiates an intense aura. Approaching these silhouettes is impossible, as they will always retreat to remain at the edge of their vision. However, a special silhouette may appear, taking the form of '''The Custodian.'''<div style="margin: 20px 0 20px 25px; border-left: 2px solid #7a6040; padding-left: 20px; color: #bcac94;">
It may appear anywhere between 100 to 999 minutes after entering the level.

It will always remain in the direct centre of their vision for as long as the wanderer stays in the field.

Approaching '''The Custodian''' will cause its form to distort violently. Words will be beamed directly into the wanderer's brain:<div style="font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; background: #0e0c08; color: #b06040; padding: 12px; margin: 15px 0; border: 1px solid #5a4030; text-align: center; letter-spacing: 2px; font-size: 1.1em; box-shadow: inset 0 0 15px #000;">
“APPROACH>>” “SEIZE>>” “PROCeEED>>” “YOU COuLD HAVE DoNE THINGS DIFFERENTLY>>”
</div>It is unknown what happens to those who disobey these commands. If the wanderer makes any noise within 100 meters of '''The Custodian''' at this stage, they will be instantly transported to the sub-level <span style="text-shadow: 4px 6px 0px #DADADA, 8px 12px 0px #AAAAAA, 9px 18px 0px #707070">'''“Once Was Known, Now Is Forgotten.”'''</span></div>

=== <span style="color: #b89070; border-bottom: 1px dotted #6a5a40; padding-bottom: 4px;">Nightfall</span> ===
A far more likely event is nightfall, which occurs when 999 '''minutes''' have elapsed in the field.

Despite the lack of a sun, a moon rises. This moon takes the appearance of a giant eyeball suspended in the centre of the sky. Simultaneously, the poppies in the field turn a dark grey and grow large eyeballs in the centres of their heads. These eyes usually mimic the colour and shape of someone close to the wanderer, and they will track their every movement. Any human on this level will experience a severe sense of fatigue the longer the eyeballs stare. Falling asleep at this stage transports them directly to the sub-level <span style="text-shadow: 4px 6px 0px #DADADA, 8px 12px 0px #AAAAAA, 9px 18px 0px #707070">'''“Once Was Known, Now Is Forgotten.”'''</span> ''<span style="color: #9a8a72; font-style: italic;">This night does not end.</span>''<div style="background: #15120e; border: 1px solid #4a3a28; padding: 15px; margin: 25px 0; font-family: 'Georgia', serif; color: #a89880; box-shadow: inset 0 0 30px #050302;">
[[RECORD CORRUPTED|IMAGE NOT FOUND:]] There are no exits on the field.

<span style="display: block; margin-top: 8px; font-size: 1.1em; letter-spacing: 1px;">''Don't think you can escape your sins that easily.''</span>
</div>

== <span style="border-left: 6px solid #8a7a50; padding-left: 15px; color: #d4c4ac; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: 2px;">Once Was Found, Now Is Known</span> ==
If the wanderer chooses to enter the house within 999 '''minutes''' of arriving, they will quickly realise there are no visible entrances. The only way inside is to crawl under the house and enter through a hatch, dropping into a cramped, maze-like crawlspace surrounded by pipes.

The pipes are warm to the touch and pulse with a rhythm identical to a human heartbeat. As the wanderer navigates the maze, muffled struggling or distant laughter, sounds from their own past, travel through the metal. If they entered the crawlspace after 99 minutes of being on the level, '''it''' may materialise within the pipes with them. While it does not pose an immediate threat at this stage, the wanderer must ignore the sound of its breathing or rushed crawling. Eventually, the pipes taper off, and they will emerge through a floorboard into the house's interior.

=== <span style="color: #b8a070;">Guilt</span> ===
The inside of the house is significantly larger than its exterior dimensions suggest. There is no limit to the number of rooms, and every room is a vague, claustrophobic recreation of the wanderer's childhood home.<div style="background: #1c1812; padding: 20px; border: 1px solid #5a4e3a; box-shadow: inset 0 0 40px #0a0804; margin: 15px 0;">
The wallpaper remains a static, dull yellow, and there are '''no doors at all.''' Ceilings are at most six and a half feet high, and hallways may narrow until they are forced to walk sideways.

All images and paintings have their faces scratched away. <span style="color: #a09078; border-bottom: 1px dotted #6a5a40;">''The M.E.G. is obliged to state that the wanderer should not attempt to recall the individuals depicted under any circumstances.''</span>

The house is not uniformly lit. Strangely, the darkest areas are near the windows rather than deep within the house. Please note that at this stage the house is seemingly infinite, or constantly changing. As such, there is no "deepest" part. Windows do not signify the actual borders of the house; they can appear in hallways or on interior walls and ceilings. Breaking an "Exterior" window and jumping out will '''not''' return the wanderer to the field. They will fall upward into a dark sky, eventually landing in the sub-level <span style="text-shadow: 4px 6px 0px #DADADA, 8px 12px 0px #AAAAAA, 9px 18px 0px #707070">'''"Once Was Known, Now Is Forgotten."'''</span>

All furniture is from the wanderer's childhood, but it feels like porcelain or cold skin to the touch. Proportions are violently distorted, either stretched unnaturally or massively enlarged.
</div>
<div style="margin: 30px 0; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #5a4e3a; padding: 10px; background: #15120c; box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px #000;">
