=== <span style="color: #b06050;">Unique Spaces</span> ===
The following rooms will invoke a severe sense of '''Jamais Vu'''. The wanderer will recognise them, but they will feel highly unfamiliar and deeply uncomfortable. These areas are extremely dangerous, as they are far more likely to encounter '''The Custodian''' here.
{| style="width:100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 20px 0;"
| style="width: 50%; border: 1px solid #4a3e2e; padding: 15px; background: rgba(25,20,15,0.8);" |<span style="color: #c09870; font-size: 1.2em;">The Kitchen</span>

* Perpetually filled with the scent of the meal the wanderer has eaten the most in their life, though the stove and oven are cold.
* "Porcelain-skin" chairs are tucked under a table that does not exist.
* A single ceramic bowl sits on the counter, filled with Blood-Red Poppies.
* <span style="color: #c07050;">Warning:</span> Eating anything found here will taste of ash and copper. Turning on the faucet releases thick, black ooze instead of water. If this ooze touches the wanderer's skin, it will stain permanently, and may cause auditory or visual hallucinations. Additionally, '''It''' and any Vassals will then be able to track their location regardless of which room or level they enter, making them "Known." If the wanderer reaches '''“Erased”''' while under the effects of the ink, their chance of survival significantly decreases.
| style="width: 50%; border: 1px solid #4a3e2e; padding: 15px; background: rgba(20,18,22,0.8);" |<span style="color: #c09870; font-size: 1.2em;">The Living Room</span>

* The sofa extends indefinitely into the shadows.
* A television from the wanderer's youth is stuck looping their most shameful memories, played back with a cartoonish, laughing studio audience track.
* '''Do not look at the framed photos.''' They are high-definition photos of the wanderer, taken from the perspective of the poppies outside. The corners of this room are unnaturally dark. If the wanderer hears a muffled cry from the darkness, they must leave immediately. The wanderer's eyes cannot linger too long on the shadows. They have a way of staring back.
|- style="vertical-align: top;"
| style="border: 1px solid #4a3e2e; padding: 15px; background: rgba(18,16,20,0.8);" |<span style="color: #c09870; font-size: 1.2em;">The Attic</span>

* Reached by pulling down a ladder that feels like cold bone. This is the only room with high ceilings, extending upward into an infinite void.
* A single wooden trunk sits in the centre. Opening it reveals a physical image of a memory, with words written on the underside. Reading these words aloud provides temporary relief against '''The Custodian,''' but the wanderer will permanently lose that memory in exchange.
| style="border: 1px solid #4a3e2e; padding: 15px; background: rgba(22,18,20,0.8);" |<span style="color: #c09870; font-size: 1.2em;">The Bedroom</span>

* A perfect, claustrophobic cube where the bed occupies 90% of the floor space. The static yellow wallpaper vibrates with a low-frequency hum that induces nausea.
* Looking into the vanity mirror will not show the wanderer's reflection. Instead, they will see a version of themself that "did things differently." This image will stare at the wanderer. '''Do not touch the glass.''' Doing so transports them to <span style="text-shadow: 4px 6px 0px #DADADA, 8px 12px 0px #AAAAAA, 9px 18px 0px #707070">'''“Once Was Known, Now Is Forgotten.”'''</span>
|}
<div style="margin: 30px 0; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #4a3020; padding: 10px; background: #0a0400;">[[File:REMEMBER_ME%3F.jpg|center|600x600px|HIM.]]<div style="color: #a07050; font-size: 0.9em; margin-top: 8px;">The Custodian.</div></div>

== <span style="border-left: 6px solid #905040; padding-left: 15px; color: #d4c4ac; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: 2px;">Failure</span> ==
During the wanderer's stay inside the house, '''it''' will grow increasingly agitated and aggressive. The Custodian is an entity that exists in the "Gaps": a tall, spindly figure with a single giant eye in the centre of its flower-shaped face and unnaturally long, disproportionate limbs. The Custodian is theorised to be separate from the level, existing as an individual entity with its own motives. 

Evidence consistently shows '''The Custodian''' to be far more aggressive toward older individuals, or those carrying high levels of guilt and depression. It is entirely non-hostile toward children under the age of 12, often assisting in their departure from the level without making itself known.

The M.E.G. has documented the following stages of '''"exposure"''':
