* If The Custodian touches the wanderer, their identity dissolves. They will forget their name, their past, and finally, their physical form. They will manifest as a silhouette in the field, joining the figures in the distance. The Custodian adopts the wanderer's physical likeness, memories, and voice, projecting a "Vassal." M.E.G. operatives are cautioned that "Wanderers" seen exiting this level may actually be instances of The Custodian. The main entity never leaves the level: only fragments of it do.
<p style="margin-bottom:15px; font-weight:bold; filter: blur(0.5px);">If The Custodian sees the wanderer, they must run and find the closest hiding spot. Do not panic at the chaotic sound of its rushing footsteps behind; prioritise refuge. Its movements destroy the environment, clawing away the wallpaper and shattering reality. If they see The Custodian in a window, they cannot approach. It will shatter the glass and crawl inside.</p>
|}

== <span style="border-left: 6px solid #6a4a6a; padding-left: 15px; color: #d4c4ac; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: 2px;">Extended Influence:</span> ==
<div style="font-family: 'Georgia', 'Times New Roman', serif; background: #1a1410; border-left: 8px solid #a35a2c; padding: 18px; margin: 30px 0; color: #d6a27a; box-shadow: inset 0 0 15px #0d0a08; font-size:1em">
'''M.E.G. ADVISORY:''' Evidence suggests The Custodian's role as a “placeholder" extends far beyond “Once Was, Now Is.” Operatives have documented encounters with entities and other personnel bearing its traits in at least <span style="color: #c09070;">seven</span> other levels and two sub‑levels. While the full scope remains classified to prevent public panic, the following patterns have been confirmed.
</div>

=== <span style="color: #b09070; border-bottom: 1px dotted #6a5a40; padding-bottom: 4px;">Cross‑Level Manifestations</span> ===
The Custodian does not physically leave "Once Was, Now Is." Instead, it projects '''Vassals,''' autonomous fragments of itself created from wanders subject to the “Identity Exchange.” These instances are indistinguishable from the original entity in appearance and behaviour, but they operate with limited autonomy and eventually dissipate if the vacancy is not filled. However, they obtain the unique ability to shapeshift to and from The Custodian’s appearance and the wanderer’s appearance at will.

