=== <span style="color: #b09070; border-bottom: 1px dotted #6a5a40; padding-bottom: 4px;"><span class="cognitive-bleed">Cognitive Bleed</span></span> ===
Individuals who have survived extended exposure to The Custodian or one of its Vassals, even without direct contact, often exhibit <span class="cognitive-bleed">'''"Cognitive Bleed"'''.</span> Symptoms include:
* Recurring dreams of the yellow house in “Once Was, Now Is” that they've never visited.
* Humming of a melody they cannot identify.
* The sensation of being watched from within reflective surfaces.
* Compulsion to visit “Once Was, Now Is” or seek out a Vassal.

In advanced stages (3-5 weeks,) the M.E.G. has designated individuals who retain symptoms as ‘Carriers’ or ‘Living Vacancies’ and mandates immediate quarantine as existing Vassals within the Backrooms will begin to seek them out. This is to prevent the development of any new Vassals. No research has been conducted on what happens to entities who exhibit <span class="cognitive-bleed">"Cognitive Bleed."</span>

=== Late stage symptoms. The following may, or may not, develop: ===

* Individuals begin to unconsciously mimic the posture and gait of deceased loved ones.
* Thickened blood.
* Inability to clot, despite thickened blood.
* Memory loss when losing blood.
* Pupils dilate and the sclera darkens.
* Hair loss.
* Inability to talk.
* Insomnia.
* Paranoia.
* Psychosis.
* Necrosis.

The end stages of <span class="cognitive-bleed">"Cognitive Bleed"</span> results in sustained bleeding from every orifice around the face, loss of limbs, and the inability to clot blood. This quickly results in death.

The full cycle of <span class="cognitive-bleed">"Cognitive Bleed"</span> takes around 4-6 weeks.

<div style="margin: 30px 0; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #4a3020; padding: 10px; background: #0a0400;">[[File:BlackOoze.jpeg|center|600x600px|Blood of individuals affected by <span class="cognitive-bleed">"Cognitive Bleed"</span> in late stages.]]<div style="color: #a07050; font-size: 0.9em; margin-top: 8px;">Blood from individuals who are under the late-stage effects of "Cognitive Bleed."</div></div>

Examining the blood leaked from individuals under late-stage effects reveals that it is the same material as <span class="censored-alt">Memory and Static Splinters</span>. This leads the M.E.G. to believe that this ‘blood’ is liquid memories although this has not been confirmed.

[[Object 1|<span class="almond-water">Almond Water</span>]] has been proven to slow and in some cases stop the development of <span class="cognitive-bleed">‘Cognitive Bleed’</span> but is ineffective in late to end stages of its progression. The only other documented method for an affected individual to be cured is by visiting ‘Once Was, Now Is’.

