== <span style="border-left: 6px solid #506040; padding-left: 15px; color: #d4c4ac; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: 2px;">Alternate State: Once Was Found, Now Remains</span> ==
If the wanderer chooses to enter the house '''after 999 minutes''' of arriving in the field, a front door will appear on the side of the house they are not currently facing. When they look away, the house will seamlessly convert into an exact, flawless replica of their childhood home (matching floors, size, garden, etc.). This change is permanent, and the structure becomes entirely indestructible.

Upon entering, the wanderer is free to leave back into the field through the front door at any time. Inside, the Kitchen functions normally, providing a constant water supply and a refrigerator endlessly stocked with their favourite meals. They will never feel fatigue here.

The wanderer will notice the TV making a muffled noise. Due to the lack of electricity, it is the only working appliance. It is stuck on a continuous loop of all their memories, accompanied by the peaceful audio of nature and birdsong.
Sitting on the sofa is The Custodian. It will be staring at the television. It does not blink, nor does it react to the wanderer's presence. They can touch The Custodian safely. It will remain permanently docile.<div style="background: #161812; border-left: 8px solid #4a5a3a; padding: 18px; margin: 30px 0; color: #b0b89c; box-shadow: inset 0 0 15px #0a0a06;">
'''M.E.G. Notice:''' ''The M.E.G. is obliged to inform those concerned that exit is no longer possible. It has separated from the main "progression" of The Backrooms and now exists as a splinter. This splinter remains within The Backrooms but does not affect the main level which remains accessible to new wanderers. Any communication devices brought into this splinter will fail and any light source will emit only monochrome light.''

<p style="margin-bottom:15px; font-weight:bold; filter: blur(0.5px);">''They are safe.''</p>
</div></div>

=== <span class="rainbow-text">Memory Splinters</span> ===
In the alternate state, Memory Splinters manifest in the walls and floors of the house as the memories being played on the television. They appear as shimmering, needle-like protrusions within the wood grain of the replica furniture or doorframes.<br>
* These splinters give easily. When touched, they dissolve into the wanderer’s skin.<br>
* They provide a hyper-realistic sensory surge. If the TV is showing a memory of a summer fair, a Memory Splinter found in the nearby coffee table might carry the exact smell of popcorn or the specific chill of a soda can. Some larger memory splinters induce hallucinations.<br>
*They bring intense, fleeting happiness, reinforcing the wanderer's desire to stay within the indestructible walls of the house.
<br>
<div style="margin-top:20px; text-align:center; font-size:0.7em; letter-spacing:5px; color:#333;">Please, forget this. Leave.</div>

=== <span style="text-shadow: 4px 6px 0px #DADADA, 8px 12px 0px #AAAAAA, 9px 18px 0px #707070">Static Splinters</span> ===
This type of splinter tends to manifest more frequently the longer you spend in the alternate state, theorised to be the alternate state becoming more detached from reality. Static Splinters occur where the replica home fails to reconcile with the void outside.
These appear as matte-black, non-reflective shards that seem to flicker in and out of existence. They are most commonly found near monochrome light sources or the edges of the front door.<br>
* If a wanderer attempts to bring an outside object (like a flashlight) near a Static Splinter, this object will not work. This implies that the object itself is “forgetting” its function.<br>
* It is theorised that The Custodian is the primary source of these splinters. As it watches the TV, it "bleeds" the static of the forgotten world into the perfect replica. To touch a Static Splinter is to feel a numbing, crushing sense of indifference after the initial sensory surge. In addition, that memory will be erased from your mind and the television.<br>
* Eventually, if enough time passes, all memory splinters will be replaced with static splinters. Only static splinters manifest as canned food and beverages in sub-level <span style="text-shadow: 4px 6px 0px #DADADA, 8px 12px 0px #AAAAAA, 9px 18px 0px #707070">'''Once Was Known, Now Is Forgotten.'''</span>
