<p>'''[00:04] S:''' Check mic. We’re in. Entry via the crawlspace in Level 0 was successful. Atmosphere is… typical? Smells like old carpet and lemon polish. I wish these suits also had a smell filter. Elias, watch the perimeter. </p>

<p>'''[00:12] E:''' Copy. Sarah, I don’t see anything apart from these stupid yellow walls. </p>

<p>'''[00:15] M:''' Scanners are flat, Elias. No heat signatures, no motion. Level is stable. </p>

<p>'''[00:28] E:''' It’s not stable. Look at the photos on the mantle. They’re changing. That’s my grandmother’s house. I shouldn't be here. </p>

<p>'''[00:45] S:''' Focus, E. Remember the briefing. The level manifests based on the strongest resonance. Why is it picking yours? Marcus, check his vitals. </p>

<p>'''[00:52] M:''' Holy… Elias, your heart rate is 140. And your weight is spiking. You're sitting at 88 on the Mnemosyne Scale. That’s nearly double ours. What are you thinking about? </p>

<p>'''[01:05] E:''' (Voice shaking) I haven't told the M.E.G. doctors everything. I thought it was forgotten. </p>

<p>'''[01:12] S:''' Nothing is forgotten in the f*****g BACKROOMS!! (Urgent) Elias, move! Behind you! </p>

<p>'''[01:14] <span style="color: #8c1d1d;">(Sound of heavy, metallic scratching against hardwood)</span>'''</p>

<p>'''[01:16] M:''' I see it! It’s IT. But… it’s ignoring us. It walked right past me. It’s headed straight for Elias. </p>

<p>'''[01:22] S:''' Open fire! Standard rounds! </p>

<p>'''[01:25] <span style="color: #8c1d1d;">(Sound of rapid gunfire. Bullets hit with a dull, wet thud, like striking clay.)</span>'''</p>

<p>'''[01:28] E:''' (Screaming) It’s not stopping! It’s tall, Sarah! It’s too tall! It’s wearing my brother’s jacket… but it doesn't have a face! Just that eye! </p>

<p>'''[01:35] <span style="color: #000; background: #000;">(STATIC INTERFERENCE - 4 SECONDS)</span>'''</p>

<p>'''[01:40] M:''' Sarah, the floor is melting around them! Not the wood… the actual space! Elias is sinking! IT is just… standing over him, humming. It sounds like a hive of bees. </p>

<p>'''[01:48] S:''' WE HAVE TO DO SOMETHING! Elias, give me your hand! </p>

<p>'''[01:52] E:''' (Calm, hollow voice) IT says the maintenance was overdue, Sarah. IT says my memories are ready to be repurposed. I have to be fixed. </p>

<p>'''[01:58] S:''' Marcus, we’re losing him! Pull the- </p>

<p>'''[02:02] <span style="color: #8c1d1d;">(A loud, vibrating frequency drowns out all speech. The sound of a door clicking shut.)</span>'''</p>

<p>'''[02:10] M:''' He’s gone. Sarah, the room is empty. Elias, IT… the hallway… it’s all gone. It’s just a blank white wall now. </p>

<p>'''[02:25] S:''' (Heavy breathing) Note for the log. The Custodian didn't even look at us. IT targeted Elias first. We’re evacuating. Now. </p>

<p>'''[02:26] M:''' It’s… not right. That one room may have changed due to the “theft,” but we’re definitely still being watched. Could it be IT targets the person with the heaviest memories first…?</p>

