|content=
<div class="fullscreen-content" style="position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; overflow-y: auto; background: #000000; font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;">

    <div style="position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; z-index: 0;">
        [[File:AngelEyeBG.jpeg|class=bg-image|link=]]
    </div>

    <div style="position: relative; z-index: 2; min-height: 100%; padding: 60px 20px; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center; color: #fff;">
        <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">

            <div class="fade-in" style="font-size: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 8px; color: #aa0000; text-shadow: 0 0 15px #ff0000;">THE HUMMING STOPPED.</div>
            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 20px 0; color: #ccc; font-style: italic;">That’s how you know IT is close. Not the silence... the pressure. The air gets heavy.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 40px 0; font-size: 1.1em;">I thought IT was in the walls again. Scratching, rearranging the insulation, smoothing out the memories like fresh plaster. I was wrong. IT's in the *floor*. I can feel IT moving beneath me, a slow, patient vibration. The wood is warm. Too warm.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 30px 0; letter-spacing: 2px; color: #b0b0b0;">Every step IT takes sounds wrong. Not like footsteps. Like a wet mop slapping tile. *Thwack. Thwack. Thwack.* And underneath that, the humming. A low, mechanical drone that makes my vision blur at the edges.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="font-size: 2em; margin: 50px 0; font-weight: bold; color: #660000; text-shadow: 0 0 20px #ff0000;">D O N ' T  B R E A T H E .</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 30px 0;">I’m wedged under the bedroom vanity. It smells like rot and my grandmother’s perfume... the one she wore to funerals. My fingers are bleeding. I tore them open trying to pry a splinter from the baseboard. A memory splinter. A sliver of *before* I could use to stay real. But the wood wouldn't give. It held on. It held on like it wanted to keep my fingerprints.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 40px 0; font-size: 1.2em; color: #ff8888;">The humming stopped right outside the door. I can see the shadow under the gap. IT's feet are too long. Too many joints. The toes curl and uncurl, tasting the air.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 30px 0; font-size: 1.5em; animation: glitch-text 0.3s infinite;">I T  K N O W S .  I T  K N O W S .  I T  K N O W S .</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 30px 0;">The door handle is turning. It doesn't click. It rotates with the sound of grinding teeth. Porcelain cracking. I’m clutching the only shard I managed to pull, a tiny piece of a birthday candle memory. The wax is still warm. I can smell the smoke. For a second, I'm not here. I'm six years old, and the cake is lit, and everyone is singing.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 30px 0; color: #aaa;">But the singing warps. The voices slow down, stretch out, become the hum. IT is siphoning it. IT drinks the warmth. IT leaves only the cold grain of the wood.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 30px 0; font-size: 1.3em;">My hand is fading. The fingers are turning translucent, the wood grain of the vanity cabinet bleeding through my skin. I'm becoming part of the furniture. Part of the house. Another splinter for IT to ignore.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 40px 0; font-size: 1.1em; font-style: italic;">IT's not looking for me. IT's looking for what I stole. My memories. The bike rides, the rain on the window, the warmth of my mother's hand. IT wants to clean them. Scrub them away until the house is blank. Sterile. Ready for the next occupant.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 50px 0; font-size: 2.5em; letter-spacing: 15px; font-weight: 900; color: #ffffff; text-shadow: 0 0 30px #ff0000;">I T ' S  I N .</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 30px 0;">The door swings open. IT fills the frame. Too tall. The ceiling groans as IT stoops, vertebrae crackling like wet twigs. Its skin is the colour of wet clay—grey and glistening. And in the centre of its head, where a face should be, there is only a single, unblinking amber eye. It pulses. It *sees*.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 30px 0;">That eye. It doesn't look at me. It looks *through* me, into the layers of wood and plaster and time that I'm becoming. IT tilts its head. The eye narrows. I think IT is trying to remember what I was.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 30px 0;">The humming starts again. Louder. It's inside my skull. My teeth are vibrating. The candle memory in my hand flickers—the flame gutters, smothered by the sound. IT reaches down. Its fingers are long, segmented, the joints bending backward. Not to grab me. To touch the floorboards where my legs used to be.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 30px 0; font-weight: bold; color: #ff4444;">I CAN’T FEEL MY LEGS. THE WOOD HAS SWALLOWED THEM. I AM UP TO MY CHEST IN THE GRAIN.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 40px 0; font-size: 1.2em;">IT runs a clay finger along the seam where my body meets the floor. A seal. IT is sealing me in. Maintenance. I am a flaw. A ruined floorboard in the narrative of the house. IT is fixing me. IT is becoming me.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 30px 0;">"Please," I try to say. But my lips are wood. My tongue is splinters. The word comes out as a creak.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 30px 0;">IT pauses. The amber eye swivels down to meet my fading gaze. For a moment, I see something behind it. Not malice. Not hunger. Just a deep, endless *clean*. The calm of a scrubbed floor. The peace of an empty room.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 40px 0; font-size: 1.1em; color: #888;">IT doesn't want me to suffer. IT doesn't want anything. IT just wants the universe to be still. To be quiet. To be *right*. Is this why IT becomes people?</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 50px 0; font-size: 3em; font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: 20px; color: #fff; text-shadow: 0 0 40px #aa0000;">I AM THE GRAIN.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 30px 0;">The humming fades. IT straightens, the eye fixed on the wall beyond me. IT turns, joints cracking, and shambles back into the hallway. It seemed... to morph into my figure. I don't know where it's going. The door doesn't close. It just ceases to matter.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 30px 0;">I am the floorboard now. I am the way the light hits the carpet. I am a rotten plank that no one will ever investigate. I am a memory of a memory, smoothed over, waxed, forgotten.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 40px 0; font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; font-style: italic;">If you walk over me, don't linger. The house is listening. IT is always listening. IT will find you, and become you, and make you an extra in the narrative forever.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin-top: 100px; font-size: 0.8em; color: #444; letter-spacing: 5px;">[ MARK WARNER: MISSING IN ACTION ]</div>
            <div class="fade-in" style="margin-top: 20px; font-size: 0.7em; color: #333;">— MARK WARNER, SPLINTER #427, RECOVERED FROM 14B —</div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
}}

