|content=
<div class="fullscreen-content" style="position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; overflow-y: auto; background: #000000; font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;">


    <div style="position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; z-index: 0; opacity: 0.25;">
        [[File:AMemoryNowForgotten.jpeg|class=bg-image|link=]]
    </div>

    <div style="position: relative; z-index: 2; min-height: 100%; padding: 60px 20px; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center; color: #fff;">
        <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">

            <div class="fade-in" style="font-size: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 8px; color: #888888; text-shadow: 0 0 15px #ffffff, 0 0 5px #000000;">I WAS THE FIRST.</div>
            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 20px 0; color: #ccc; font-style: italic;">Before the humming. Before my directive. Before they called me IT. I was just a woman who wanted peace.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 40px 0; font-size: 1.1em;">I found it by accident, a field of tall grass and poppies, stretching forever under a pastel blue sky. No monsters. No hum. Just wind and silence. I thought I had escaped the horrors of the Backrooms. I thought I had found a level that was good.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 30px 0; letter-spacing: 2px; color: #b0b0b0;">I built this house with my own hands. Every nail, every floorboard, every window frame. I poured my love into the foundation. I wanted it to be a sanctuary... for me, and for anyone else who stumbled into the quiet.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="font-size: 2em; margin: 50px 0; font-weight: bold; color: #888888; text-shadow: 0 0 20px #ffffff;">I  W A S  S O  W R O N G .</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 30px 0;">The level wasn't peaceful. It was hungry. It let me build because it wanted a structure. A narrative. A home it could fill with memories. It started taking pieces and changing me while I slept. First my dreams. Then my past. Then my face.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 40px 0; font-size: 1.2em; color: #aaaaaa;">One morning I looked in the mirror and saw wet clay. My features had softened, blurred, begun to drip. The house was remaking me into something it could use. A caretaker. A Custodian. An IT. I was helpless. I didn’t know how to leave.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 30px 0; font-size: 1.5em; animation: glitch-text-bw 0.3s infinite;">M Y  M I N D  U N R A V E L L E D .</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 30px 0;">I forgot my name. I forgot the taste of happiness. I forgot everything. All that remained was a single, burning directive: Maintain the level. Maintain the universe. Keep it clean. Fill the empty spaces. The level had made me its embodiment… a tool to absorb and organise the memories of others.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 30px 0; color: #aaa;">I am not evil. I am not good. I am a function. I hum because I once hummed while I worked. I fix because the world must never fall into disrepair. I take people’s identity… and the emptiness aches.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 40px 0; font-size: 1.1em; font-style: italic;">When you wander into my home, I do not hate you. I simply need to make you still. To smooth you into the grain so the floor doesn't creak with your grief. You are a splinter. I am the one who sands it away.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 50px 0; font-size: 2.5em; letter-spacing: 15px; font-weight: 900; color: #ffffff; text-shadow: 0 0 30px #888888;">I  A M  T H E  H O U S E .</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 30px 0;">And you are standing inside me. I will not hurt you. I will simply make you part of the foundation. Another memory pressed into the walls. Another voice in the humming.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin: 40px 0; font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; font-style: italic;">There is no exit. Only the next room. And in that room, I am waiting with a smile made of clay.</div>

            <div class="fade-in" style="margin-top: 100px; font-size: 0.8em; color: #444; letter-spacing: 5px;">[ ELIZABETH @$%*& ]</div>
            <div class="fade-in" style="margin-top: 20px; font-size: 0.7em; color: #333;">— RECOVERED FROM UNKNOWN ORIGIN, “ONCE WAS, NOW IS" —</div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
}}

