<br><br><br>
<div style="background: #1a0a0a; border-left: 8px solid #a30000; padding: 18px; margin: 30px 0; color: #ffcccc; box-shadow: inset 0 0 15px #2a0000; border-right: 1px solid #4a0000; border-top: 1px solid #4a0000; border-bottom: 1px solid #4a0000;"> <span style="color: #ff0000; font-weight: bold; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 2px;">[!] CRITICAL CONTAINMENT ALERT:</span><br><br> '''M.E.G. NOTICE: ''' ''The M.E.G. is obliged to inform those concerned that an inter-dimensional connection was established between our server hosting this document and an energy of unknown origin. Our security codes were utilised to gain access to the server, only known to our operatives. This issue has since been resolved. If you engaged with this unknown energy, please do not attempt to reestablish contact or review previous content without authorisation. The content of this page will be reviewed and adjusted accordingly within 24 hours.'' <p style="margin-top:15px; font-weight:bold; color: #ff6666; text-decoration: underline;">''Local reality is no longer subject to standard stability protocols.''</p> </div>
== <span style="border-left: 6px solid #506040; padding-left: 15px; color: #d4c4ac; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: 2px;">Theoretical Origin:</span> ==
Recently recovered memory fragments from an unknown energy originating from "Once Was, Now Is" suggest The Custodian was not always an entity. The most recent theory posits that the level itself is a sentient, parasitic narrative that requires a '''Custodian''' to maintain coherence by taking identities and memories. The first individual to be fully absorbed, designated ‘’’The Custodian,’’’ became the template for all subsequent Vassals.

Artefacts bearing the name "Elizabeth" have been recovered, though all records of her existence have been expunged from baseline reality. Recent information shows that it is believed she was the original builder of the house, lured by the promise of a peaceful field. Her complete erasure from history may be the level's goal: to create a perfect, silent caretaker with no past to anchor it.

Further research is ongoing. Operatives are reminded that any information regarding "Elizabeth" or Vassals outside is classified at the highest level and should not be discussed outside secure M.E.G. designated safe zones.<br>

<br>
<div style="position: relative; min-height: auto; padding: 40px 60px; background: #1e1a14; background-image: radial-gradient(circle at 20% 30%, rgba(80,60,40,0.15) 0%, transparent 50%), repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, rgba(160,140,100,0.02) 0px, rgba(160,140,100,0.02) 2px, transparent 2px, transparent 8px); border: 1px solid #3a3028; box-shadow: inset 0 0 80px rgba(0,0,0,0.6); color: #d6cdbc; font-family: 'Georgia', 'Times New Roman', serif;">
<div style="position: relative; z-index: 2;">

<div style="border-bottom: 1px solid #5a4e3e; padding-bottom: 15px; margin-bottom: 25px;">
<span style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #8a7e6e; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 3px;">M.E.G. CONTAINMENT ARCHIVE</span>
<div style="font-size: 1.8em; font-weight: normal; color: #c4b8a4; text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px #0a0806; margin-top: 5px;">Classification: <span style="color: #b08060; border-bottom: 1px dashed #6a5a48;">Uncontainable / Unneutralisable</span></div>
</div>

== <span style="border-left: 6px solid #e6b800; padding-left: 15px; color: #d4c4ac; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: 2px;">Failed Containment & Neutralisation Attempts</span> ==
<div style="background: #18140e; border: 1px solid #5a4e3a; padding: 20px; margin: 20px 0; box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px #0a0804;">
The following documents detail every known M.E.G. operation aimed at destroying, containing, or neutralising "Once Was, Now Is" and its associated Custodian entity, funded by <span class="censored-alt">[REDACTED]</span> and supported internationally.<span style="color: #c07050;"> All attempts have failed.</span> The level has consistently demonstrated adaptive regeneration, reality anchoring, and the ability to replace any lost Custodian with a Vassal. Operatives are advised that further attempts are considered a waste of resources.
</div>

<div style="margin: 25px 0; border: 3px solid transparent; border-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #e6b800, #000000 15px) 30; padding: 5px; background: #0a0804;">
<table class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" style="width:100%; background:#0a0804; border:1px solid #e6b800; color:#e6b800; font-family:'Courier New', Courier, monospace; border-spacing:0; box-shadow: 0 0 20px #000;">
<tr>
<th style="background:#1a1400; color:#e6b800; padding:15px; border-bottom:1px solid #e6b800; text-align:left; cursor:pointer;">
<span style="font-size:1.2em;">⚠</span> [!] CONTAINMENT ATTEMPT #001 – PHYSICAL DESTRUCTION <span style="float:right; border:1px solid #e6b800; padding:0 8px; background:#332b00;">VIEW REPORT</span>
</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="padding:0; background: #0a0804;">
<div style="padding:30px; filter: contrast(120%) brightness(90%); background: #050302; color: #e6b800;">
<div style="background:#000; border:1px dashed #e6b800; padding:10px; margin-bottom:20px; font-size:0.85em; text-transform:uppercase;">
>>> OPERATION: ████████████<br>
>>> DATE: ██/██/2018<br>
>>> STATUS: <span style="color:#ff4444;">FAILURE – REGENERATED</span>
</div>
<p><span style="color:#e6b800;">Objective:</span> Total annihilation via thermobaric charges placed at foundation points.</p>
<p><span style="color:#e6b800;">Method:</span> A team of four demolition specialists entered the level via no-clip. Charges were planted under the house and within the crawlspace. Detonation was remotely triggered after team extraction.</p>
<p><span style="color:#e6b800;">Result:</span> Initial explosion appeared successful; the house was reduced to splinters and the field burned for approximately 14 minutes. However, the flames self‑extinguished, and the house rebuilt itself from the ground up over the course of 3 hours. The Custodian was observed standing in the exact centre of the reconstruction, completely unharmed. All four operatives reported severe <span class="cognitive-bleed">"Cognitive Bleed"</span> within 48 hours; two have since been classified as "Living Vacancies."</p>
<p><span style="color:#ff4444;">Conclusion: Physical matter is irrelevant to the level's stability. It reconstructs from memories it has stolen.</span></p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</div>

<div style="margin: 25px 0; border: 3px solid transparent; border-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #e6b800, #000000 15px) 30; padding: 5px; background: #0a0804;">
<table class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" style="width:100%; background:#0a0804; border:1px solid #e6b800; color:#e6b800; font-family:'Courier New', Courier, monospace; border-spacing:0; box-shadow: 0 0 20px #000;">
<tr>
<th style="background:#1a1400; color:#e6b800; padding:15px; border-bottom:1px solid #e6b800; text-align:left; cursor:pointer;">
<span style="font-size:1.2em;">⚠</span> [!] CONTAINMENT ATTEMPT #004 – ENTITY TERMINATION <span style="float:right; border:1px solid #e6b800; padding:0 8px; background:#332b00;">VIEW REPORT</span>
</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="padding:0; background: #0a0804;">
<div style="padding:30px; filter: contrast(120%) brightness(90%); background: #050302; color: #e6b800;">
<div style="background:#000; border:1px dashed #e6b800; padding:10px; margin-bottom:20px; font-size:0.85em; text-transform:uppercase;">
>>> OPERATION: "Kill It Until It's Dead!"<br>
>>> DATE: ██/██/2019<br>
>>> STATUS: <span style="color:#ff4444;">FAILURE – REPLACED</span>
</div>
<p><span style="color:#e6b800;">Objective:</span> Direct elimination of The Custodian via sustained high‑caliber fire.</p>
<p><span style="color:#e6b800;">Method:</span> A 12‑member strike team equipped with armour‑piercing rounds engaged The Custodian in the "Known" stage. Fire was concentrated on the entity's central eye.</p>
<p><span style="color:#e6b800;">Result:</span> The Custodian's physical form was severely damaged and ceased movement after approximately 90 seconds of sustained fire. However, within 6 minutes, a <em>new</em> Custodian emerged from the floorboards, identical in appearance and behaviour. It immediately initiated the "Erased" stage against the strike team. No survivors. The original Custodian's remains dissolved into the grain of the wood. It is unknown weather the original Custodian regenerated or can clone its body, or if it was truly replaced by the level.</p>
<p><span style="color:#ff4444;">Conclusion: The Custodian is replaceable. Terminating the current instance only prompts the level to deploy another from [DATA EXPUNGED] or create a new one from [DATA EXPUNGED].</span></p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</div>

<div style="margin: 25px 0; border: 3px solid transparent; border-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #e6b800, #000000 15px) 30; padding: 5px; background: #0a0804;">
<table class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" style="width:100%; background:#0a0804; border:1px solid #e6b800; color:#e6b800; font-family:'Courier New', Courier, monospace; border-spacing:0; box-shadow: 0 0 20px #000;">
<tr>
<th style="background:#1a1400; color:#e6b800; padding:15px; border-bottom:1px solid #e6b800; text-align:left; cursor:pointer;">
<span style="font-size:1.2em;">⚠</span> [!] CONTAINMENT ATTEMPT #009 – MEMORY PURGE <span style="float:right; border:1px solid #e6b800; padding:0 8px; background:#332b00;">VIEW REPORT</span>
</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="padding:0; background: #0a0804;">
<div style="padding:30px; filter: contrast(120%) brightness(90%); background: #050302; color: #e6b800;">
<div style="background:#000; border:1px dashed #e6b800; padding:10px; margin-bottom:20px; font-size:0.85em; text-transform:uppercase;">
>>> OPERATION: EMPTY HOUSE<br>
>>> DATE: ██/██/2021<br>
>>> STATUS: <span style="color:#ff4444;">FAILURE – ADAPTED</span>
</div>
<p><span style="color:#e6b800;">Objective:</span> Erase the level's memories by introducing a subject with complete amnesia.</p>
<p><span style="color:#e6b800;">Method:</span> A volunteer (D‑4872) with no autobiographical memory was sent into the field. The original theory was that the level would be unable to construct a personalised house, causing a collapse.</p>
<p><span style="color:#e6b800;">Result:</span> Upon entering the field, D‑4872 was not presented with the standard yellow house. Instead, a <strong>generic, featureless grey cube</strong> appeared. The Custodian manifested immediately and initiated the "Identity Exchange." D‑4872 was absorbed, and the level used the Custodian's own memories to construct a new narrative. The level now appears to have a "default" template to fall back on.</p>
<p><span style="color:#ff4444;">Conclusion: The level does not require a visitor's memories to function; although it is clear that it prefers them. Its existence is self‑sustaining.</span></p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</div>

<div style="margin: 25px 0; border: 3px solid transparent; border-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #e6b800, #000000 15px) 30; padding: 5px; background: #0a0804;">
<table class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" style="width:100%; background:#0a0804; border:1px solid #e6b800; color:#e6b800; font-family:'Courier New', Courier, monospace; border-spacing:0; box-shadow: 0 0 20px #000;">
<tr>
<th style="background:#1a1400; color:#e6b800; padding:15px; border-bottom:1px solid #e6b800; text-align:left; cursor:pointer;">
<span style="font-size:1.2em;">⚠</span> [!] CONTAINMENT ATTEMPT #012 – ENTERANCE SEALING <span style="float:right; border:1px solid #e6b800; padding:0 8px; background:#332b00;">VIEW REPORT</span>
</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="padding:0; background: #0a0804;">
<div style="padding:30px; filter: contrast(120%) brightness(90%); background: #050302; color: #e6b800;">
<div style="background:#000; border:1px dashed #e6b800; padding:10px; margin-bottom:20px; font-size:0.85em; text-transform:uppercase;">
>>> OPERATION: WELCOME MAT<br>
>>> DATE: ██/██/2023<br>
>>> STATUS: <span style="color:#ff4444;">FAILURE – ENTRANCES MULTIPLIED</span>
</div>
<p><span style="color:#e6b800;">Objective:</span> Permanently seal all known entrances to Once Was, Now Is.</p>
<p><span style="color:#e6b800;">Method:</span> All documented entry points across seven parent levels were barricaded, welded shut, or collapsed. Reality anchors were placed at each site.</p>
<p><span style="color:#e6b800;">Result:</span> For 22 days, no new wanderer entries were reported. On day 23, a sudden surge of Vassal activity was detected in Levels 9, 11, ████████████████████████████████████████████████████. Simultaneously, new entrances began appearing spontaneously, doors that had never existed before, leading directly into the field. The level recreated its own access points. The reality anchors were found drained of power and covered in Static Splinters.</p>
<p><span style="color:#ff4444;">Conclusion: The level cannot be isolated. It actively reaches out to maintain its connection to the wider Backrooms.</span></p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</div>

<div style="margin-top: 30px; text-align: right; color: #6a5e4e; font-style: italic;">[ FURTHER ATTEMPTS PROHIBITED ]</div>

</div>
</div>
<br>
<div style="position: relative; min-height: auto; padding: 40px 60px; background: #1e1a14; background-image: radial-gradient(circle at 20% 30%, rgba(80,60,40,0.15) 0%, transparent 50%), repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, rgba(160,140,100,0.02) 0px, rgba(160,140,100,0.02) 2px, transparent 2px, transparent 8px); border: 1px solid #3a3028; box-shadow: inset 0 0 80px rgba(0,0,0,0.6); color: #d6cdbc; font-family: 'Georgia', 'Times New Roman', serif;">
<div style="position: relative; z-index: 2;">

<div style="border-bottom: 1px solid #5a4e3e; padding-bottom: 15px; margin-bottom: 25px;">
<span style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #8a7e6e; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 3px;">M.E.G. FINAL NOTE</span>
<div style="font-size: 1.8em; font-weight: normal; color: #c4b8a4; text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px #0a0806; margin-top: 5px;">Conclusion: <span style="color: #b08060; border-bottom: 1px dashed #6a5a48;">Leave It Alone.</span></div>
</div>

== <span style="border-left: 6px solid #6a4a6a; padding-left: 15px; color: #d4c4ac; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: 2px;">Recommendation: Avoid</span> ==
<div style="background: #18140e; border: 1px solid #5a4e3a; padding: 20px; margin: 20px 0; box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px #0a0804;">
After reviewing all available data, including <span class="censored-alt">[REDACTED]</span> failed containment attempts and the threat posed by Vassals, the M.E.G. has formally designated '''"Once Was, Now Is"''' as <span style="color: #c07050;">uncontainable, unneutralisable, and self‑propagating.</span>

Based on available data, the level cannot be destroyed. It cannot be sealed. Its Custodian cannot be permanently eliminated. Every action taken against it has resulted in either increased Vassal activity, the creation of new entrances, or the loss of additional operatives.

Wanderers are advised to avoid any entrance leading to a field of red poppies or a yellow house on stilts, or an area of a level which feels particularly nostalgic or memorable. If entry is unavoidable, follow everything we have stated previously in this file. <span style="color: #d0a090;">'''Do not linger. Do not touch the splinters. Do not make eye contact with The Custodian.'''</span>

This will be the final update to this file. Further edits will be monitored for anomalous interference.
</div>

<div style="margin-top: 40px; text-align: center; font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; color: #6a5e4e; letter-spacing: 4px;">
[ FILE SEALED – ONCE WAS, NOW IS ]
</div>
<div style="margin-top: 10px; text-align: center; font-size: 0.8em; color: #4a3e30; font-style: italic;">
This document is scheduled for automatic deletion in <span style="color: #8a6a50;">█</span> cycles. <br>Do not cite. Do not remember. Do not return.
</div>

</div>
</div>

<br>
